1
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:44,800
=Love Story in the 1970s=

2
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:47,940
=Episode 3=

3
00:02:21,820 --> 00:02:22,730
Ms. Chen.

4
00:02:23,990 --> 00:02:25,280
Do you think

5
00:02:26,570 --> 00:02:28,690
I'm just not meant for university?

6
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:32,190
If even that comes down to fate,

7
00:02:34,690 --> 00:02:37,310
then maybe it's not worth going at all.

8
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:41,850
But when you taught us,

9
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:43,090
that's not what you said.

10
00:02:44,260 --> 00:02:45,790
If I hadn't read your essays,

11
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,930
I wouldn't have dreamed of literature.

12
00:02:48,660 --> 00:02:51,030
If you hadn't always encouraged us

13
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:52,410
to study hard,

14
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:53,890
to go to university,

15
00:02:54,290 --> 00:02:56,730
so we could see
a bigger world out there,

16
00:02:57,340 --> 00:02:58,730
I wouldn't be this stubborn

17
00:02:58,730 --> 00:02:59,670
about getting in.

18
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,500
So now it's on me?

19
00:03:15,690 --> 00:03:16,840
Where there's a will,

20
00:03:17,410 --> 00:03:18,780
there's a way.

21
00:03:19,410 --> 00:03:21,410
Burn your bridges,

22
00:03:22,130 --> 00:03:25,340
and even the Qin strongholds
will fall to Chu.

23
00:03:26,820 --> 00:03:28,410
Heaven rewards...

24
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:30,780
- those who persevere.
- Heaven rewards those who persevere.

25
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:32,660
Endure hardship,

26
00:03:32,660 --> 00:03:35,570
and three thousand
Yue soldiers can conquer Wu.

27
00:03:42,340 --> 00:03:44,820
The world's changing too fast.

28
00:03:44,820 --> 00:03:46,340
These days, I don't even know

29
00:03:46,730 --> 00:03:49,460
if pushing you
toward university back then

30
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:54,260
was right or wrong.

31
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:56,410
Either way,

32
00:03:56,980 --> 00:03:58,730
you were the only one

33
00:03:58,730 --> 00:04:00,060
who supported me going.

34
00:04:01,540 --> 00:04:03,410
Whenever I started to lose faith,

35
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,660
you kept encouraging me.

36
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:06,570
So please,

37
00:04:07,450 --> 00:04:08,890
you can't waver now.

38
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:14,780
Alright.

39
00:04:16,460 --> 00:04:17,930
Then I'll be

40
00:04:18,660 --> 00:04:19,950
a pine tree

41
00:04:20,810 --> 00:04:21,900
on the highest peak,

42
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:24,080
always standing behind you.

43
00:04:33,970 --> 00:04:35,240
Rehabilitation Plan.

44
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:36,490
First,

45
00:04:37,170 --> 00:04:38,370
physical exercise.

46
00:04:38,370 --> 00:04:40,100
Daily walks and sun exposure.

47
00:04:40,860 --> 00:04:44,340
Second, memory training.
Read the newspaper every day.

48
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:46,190
(Rehabilitation Plan)
Finish one book a week.

49
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:48,250
Third, improve nutrition.

50
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,520
At least one meal
of refined grains a day.

51
00:04:50,730 --> 00:04:52,100
Meat once every two weeks.

52
00:04:52,420 --> 00:04:52,960
Fei Ni.

53
00:04:53,790 --> 00:04:54,990
What are you doing up so late?

54
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:56,250
Who are you talking to?

55
00:04:56,930 --> 00:04:58,650
I'm just reading.

56
00:04:58,650 --> 00:04:59,880
Go to sleep.

57
00:05:00,004 --> 00:05:00,950
Don't stay up too late.

58
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:09,410
Forget it.

59
00:05:11,370 --> 00:05:13,690
Meat once a week...

60
00:05:16,490 --> 00:05:17,860
And fruit.

61
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:20,420
(Meat and fruit once a week)

62
00:05:42,290 --> 00:05:45,860
(This money has to be sent
to my brother every month.)

63
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,170
(I can't touch it.)

64
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:52,450
(This is the family's
monthly living expenses.)

65
00:05:54,982 --> 00:05:56,190
(I can't touch this either.)

66
00:05:59,137 --> 00:05:59,900
(University Fund)

67
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:00,930
(Definitely not.)

68
00:06:01,610 --> 00:06:03,610
(I've saved this for three years.)

69
00:06:03,715 --> 00:06:06,420
(It's for my parents' living expenses
once I get into university.)

70
00:06:06,420 --> 00:06:07,810
(I absolutely cannot touch it.)

71
00:06:08,690 --> 00:06:11,490
(But meat and supplements cost money.)

72
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:14,420
(Should I borrow some from Ms. Xu?)

73
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:15,860
(No. No. No.)

74
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:18,100
(I can't ask the superior for money...)

75
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,520
(If word gets out later,)

76
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,930
(my commendation will be gone.)

77
00:06:23,210 --> 00:06:24,300
(What am I going to do...)

78
00:06:29,090 --> 00:06:31,471
(University Fund)
(This time, I'll have to dip into it.)

79
00:06:31,537 --> 00:06:33,860
(Otherwise Fang Muyang will really
be taken by his sister.)

80
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:35,610
(And my chance at university is gone!)

81
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:07,370
Fang Muyang.

82
00:07:07,370 --> 00:07:10,420
You have to get better this time.

83
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,780
(Inpatient Department)

84
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:18,630
Fang Muyang.

85
00:07:19,150 --> 00:07:20,810
Can you come down first?

86
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,580
Whatever you want, just tell me.

87
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:25,950
Come down first.

88
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,648
I'm waiting for Fei Ni.

89
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:29,160
It's always about Fei Ni.

90
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,110
Is that all you know?

91
00:07:30,110 --> 00:07:31,471
Does Fei Ni owe you something?

92
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,120
Cut it out.

93
00:07:33,860 --> 00:07:35,280
Alright, don't move!

94
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:37,660
I'll go get Fei Ni. Just don't move.

95
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:39,448
- I'll go find Fei Ni for you.
- Fang Muyang!

96
00:07:40,340 --> 00:07:41,810
Come down now.

97
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:43,510
Fei Ni!

98
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:45,340
Why are you sitting up there?

99
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:46,310
Quick, come down.

100
00:07:47,170 --> 00:07:47,730
Hurry.

101
00:07:50,010 --> 00:07:50,930
What's going on?

102
00:07:52,770 --> 00:07:53,630
She's taking me away.

103
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,090
I don't know her.

104
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:08,660
You're still smiling?

105
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,370
That was dangerous.

106
00:08:10,471 --> 00:08:10,980
Come here.

107
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:12,980
I'll talk to her, alright?

108
00:08:12,980 --> 00:08:14,200
Sit here.

109
00:08:14,590 --> 00:08:16,540
Head Nurse,
could you watch him for a bit?

110
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:17,420
Alright.

111
00:08:17,420 --> 00:08:19,220
- Go on, we've got him.
- Okay.

112
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:20,800
Don't go up the window ledge.

113
00:09:20,693 --> 00:09:22,820
(Rehabilitation Plan)
This is the recovery plan

114
00:09:22,820 --> 00:09:24,537
I've prepared for Fang Muyang.

115
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:26,770
Dr. Liang said

116
00:09:27,580 --> 00:09:29,400
he's only lost his memory.

117
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,180
His cognitive ability is fine.

118
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,540
So I'll start

119
00:09:32,540 --> 00:09:34,450
by teaching him basic life skills,

120
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:36,780
(Rehabilitation Plan)
until he can take care of himself.

121
00:09:37,650 --> 00:09:40,680
If he regains his memory along the way,

122
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:41,950
that would be ideal.

123
00:09:42,180 --> 00:09:43,390
But if he doesn't,

124
00:09:44,382 --> 00:09:46,226
he'll still be able to live normally.

125
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:48,100
So,

126
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:51,060
could you not send him
to a sanatorium?

127
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:52,810
I know

128
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,730
you can't bear to either.

129
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:01,100
Do you see me
the same way the other nurses do?

130
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:02,690
Like I'm cold-blooded?

131
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:05,580
You have your own difficulties, too.

132
00:10:06,610 --> 00:10:08,080
Honestly, I admire you.

133
00:10:09,930 --> 00:10:11,120
If it were someone else,

134
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:13,110
they might not be as...

135
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:14,180
clear-headed.

136
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,470
Clear-headed?

137
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,370
You mean selfish.

138
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:21,315
There's nothing wrong with that.

139
00:10:22,370 --> 00:10:24,210
You've already done the best you can

140
00:10:24,450 --> 00:10:25,460
within your means.

141
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,130
No one has the right

142
00:10:27,130 --> 00:10:29,570
to ask you to sacrifice yourself
for someone else.

143
00:10:31,090 --> 00:10:32,350
Not even your own brother.

144
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,270
Then what about you?

145
00:10:36,060 --> 00:10:38,370
Why are you willing
to give up your time

146
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,700
to look after him?

147
00:10:42,060 --> 00:10:43,840
It's not a sacrifice. I...

148
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:45,760
I truly admire...

149
00:10:47,610 --> 00:10:49,700
Fang Muyang.

150
00:10:49,980 --> 00:10:51,060
So don't worry.

151
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:53,420
I'll take the best possible care of him.

152
00:10:57,690 --> 00:10:58,730
My brother...

153
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,650
He's never done
anything to be proud of.

154
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,026
And now he's become a hero.

155
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:09,640
I'm counting on you.

156
00:11:12,980 --> 00:11:18,660
(Jiangcheng)

157
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:23,250
Excuse me. Passing through.

158
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:27,300
Excuse me. Passing through.

159
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:36,980
Comrade.

160
00:11:38,204 --> 00:11:39,140
- Thanks.
- Excuse me.

161
00:11:39,140 --> 00:11:40,610
Alright. Comrade.

162
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:44,060
Hello, that's my seat.

163
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:47,026
Hey, watch your hands.

164
00:11:48,370 --> 00:11:49,300
Please move.

165
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:50,640
That's my seat.

166
00:11:51,540 --> 00:11:52,770
You're funny.

167
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:55,180
On a train, whoever sits first owns it.

168
00:11:55,370 --> 00:11:56,580
Since when is it yours?

169
00:11:59,610 --> 00:12:00,860
It is my seat.

170
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:02,140
There's a seat number on it.

171
00:12:05,180 --> 00:12:06,070
Not anymore.

172
00:12:12,650 --> 00:12:14,010
Get up.

173
00:12:14,180 --> 00:12:15,010
You... you...

174
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:16,010
Thug.

175
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:17,650
People like you

176
00:12:17,650 --> 00:12:19,680
have no morals, no shame.

177
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:22,410
(Qu Hua)
All you do is bully the weak.

178
00:12:22,410 --> 00:12:24,350
If the one sitting here today
were a six-foot man,

179
00:12:24,350 --> 00:12:25,410
would you still dare?

180
00:12:25,410 --> 00:12:26,880
How can a scum like you

181
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,090
even get to live in this world?

182
00:12:28,090 --> 00:12:30,000
You're worse than a toad in a cesspit.

183
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,700
At least a toad eats pests!

184
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:32,410
But you?

185
00:12:32,410 --> 00:12:34,580
You're like flies, mosquitoes,
and bedbugs!

186
00:12:34,580 --> 00:12:35,780
All you do is disgust people

187
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:37,010
and waste resources.

188
00:12:37,010 --> 00:12:38,860
What gives you the right?

189
00:12:39,650 --> 00:12:40,690
How do people like you

190
00:12:41,290 --> 00:12:41,950
get to

191
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:43,490
run around

192
00:12:43,490 --> 00:12:44,700
bullying people?

193
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:47,250
(He has never harmed anyone,)

194
00:12:47,370 --> 00:12:49,460
(yet he has to suffer like that!)

195
00:12:49,820 --> 00:12:50,830
Why?

196
00:12:51,820 --> 00:12:53,410
How dare you hit me?

197
00:12:53,410 --> 00:12:55,650
Hey, don't yell at her!

198
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:00,890
Everyone saw that.

199
00:13:00,890 --> 00:13:01,820
I didn't touch her.

200
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:02,890
I didn't do anything!

201
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:04,820
Make way, please.

202
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:05,410
Make way.

203
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:06,740
I'm a doctor. Please move aside.

204
00:13:07,010 --> 00:13:08,120
Keep the air flowing.

205
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,100
Make way, please.

206
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:34,671
You're awake.

207
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,300
Who are you?

208
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,010
How did I end up here?

209
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,560
I'm a doctor.

210
00:13:45,871 --> 00:13:47,130
Your blood sugar was too low.

211
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,220
And you got overly agitated just now.

212
00:13:49,380 --> 00:13:50,220
So, you fainted.

213
00:13:50,710 --> 00:13:51,950
But it's nothing serious.

214
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:55,230
Have some sugar and get proper rest.

215
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:57,770
Thank you.

216
00:14:01,110 --> 00:14:02,860
This is my berth.

217
00:14:03,180 --> 00:14:04,280
You can lie here.

218
00:14:04,610 --> 00:14:06,360
I'll go sit in your seat later.

219
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:08,220
I can't do that.

220
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:09,940
Treating patients is my responsibility.

221
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,580
You need to rest right now.

222
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:13,180
I can't take advantage of you.

223
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,740
Besides, you said I'm fine.

224
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:19,026
If you insist on leaving,

225
00:14:19,071 --> 00:14:20,271
(Biscuits)
have this.

226
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:30,160
I'm getting off at the next stop.

227
00:14:30,540 --> 00:14:32,240
I've already spoken to the conductor.

228
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:34,370
He'll come find you later

229
00:14:34,370 --> 00:14:36,000
to top up the sleeper ticket

230
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,730
for the rest of your journey.

231
00:14:58,060 --> 00:14:58,680
No need.

232
00:15:07,970 --> 00:15:08,690
Thank you.

233
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:17,790
You study mathematics?

234
00:15:24,770 --> 00:15:25,770
When you fainted earlier,

235
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:27,280
while I was carrying you up,

236
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:29,370
the things in your bag fell out.

237
00:15:29,370 --> 00:15:31,460
(Jiangcheng University Staff ID)

238
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:45,250
Get some proper rest.

239
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:46,380
I'll leave you be.

240
00:16:10,730 --> 00:16:12,560
(Director Wu, I've made up my mind.)

241
00:16:13,450 --> 00:16:14,560
I'm going to cut ties

242
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:16,293
with my “Black Five
Categories” parents.

243
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,840
These are all the letters and photos

244
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:19,700
they sent me.

245
00:16:20,390 --> 00:16:21,550
Please trust

246
00:16:21,582 --> 00:16:23,693
(Professor Wu)
my loyalty to the revolutionary cause.

247
00:16:23,830 --> 00:16:24,980
And please believe

248
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:27,220
that I'm willing to devote my life

249
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:28,648
to our nation's mathematics.

250
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,780
I'm applying
to remain at the university.

251
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,390
Even doing odd jobs is fine.

252
00:17:40,140 --> 00:17:43,460
(Advanced Mathematics)

253
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:53,100
I heard from your sister
that you like drawing.

254
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,230
I bought these for you.

255
00:17:56,420 --> 00:17:59,900
(Colored Pencils)

256
00:18:01,260 --> 00:18:02,980
(Watercolors)

257
00:18:10,770 --> 00:18:13,060
(Fang Muyang never stuck
with anything growing up.)

258
00:18:13,540 --> 00:18:14,920
Except for drawing.

259
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:16,500
He's kept at it all these years.

260
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:17,610
If possible,

261
00:18:17,610 --> 00:18:19,020
get him a sketchbook.

262
00:18:19,490 --> 00:18:21,450
It might help his memory recover sooner.

263
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:26,410
Thank you.

264
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:27,840
Fei Ni.

265
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:30,000
Use them sparingly.

266
00:18:30,090 --> 00:18:31,990
These art supplies aren't cheap.

267
00:18:33,610 --> 00:18:36,080
When I saw your sister off
at the station,

268
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:38,004
she left you a hundred yuan.

269
00:18:39,980 --> 00:18:40,890
Can you manage money?

270
00:18:48,260 --> 00:18:49,040
Forget it.

271
00:18:49,780 --> 00:18:51,950
I'll hold onto it for you.

272
00:18:51,950 --> 00:18:53,120
In case you get scammed again.

273
00:18:53,580 --> 00:18:56,093
Don't worry, I won't spend a cent of it.

274
00:18:57,770 --> 00:18:58,560
If you like it,

275
00:18:59,004 --> 00:19:00,137
it's all yours.

276
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:01,560
Don't talk nonsense.

277
00:19:02,260 --> 00:19:04,110
Taking advantage of a hero?

278
00:19:04,510 --> 00:19:05,700
You could get me into trouble.

279
00:19:06,410 --> 00:19:06,920
Alright.

280
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:08,550
No more nonsense.

281
00:19:11,690 --> 00:19:12,740
Anyway,

282
00:19:13,390 --> 00:19:14,170
if there's anything

283
00:19:14,340 --> 00:19:16,930
you feel like eating, just tell me.

284
00:19:17,050 --> 00:19:18,410
I'll take good care of you.

285
00:19:18,650 --> 00:19:20,720
But you've got to try hard
to remember the past.

286
00:19:21,190 --> 00:19:23,680
When your sister comes again,
you have to tell her

287
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:26,040
I've been taking good care of you.

288
00:19:27,430 --> 00:19:27,820
Sure.

289
00:19:37,020 --> 00:19:40,900
(Jiangnan Station)

290
00:19:47,460 --> 00:19:48,170
Hello.

291
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:50,780
The conductor never came.

292
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:53,180
So I figured
you didn't get off early after all.

293
00:19:56,580 --> 00:19:57,580
This is the sleeper fare.

294
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:02,960
Thank you.

295
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:14,960
Watch and learn.

296
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:17,410
Cut along this line.

297
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:20,860
Don't go past it.

298
00:20:21,050 --> 00:20:22,240
Or you'll bleed.

299
00:20:30,140 --> 00:20:31,550
There, one nail done.

300
00:20:34,810 --> 00:20:35,300
Not hard.

301
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:36,600
Your turn.

302
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:40,020
Slowly.

303
00:20:40,330 --> 00:20:40,780
Okay.

304
00:20:50,271 --> 00:20:51,382
What are you doing?

305
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,040
You...

306
00:20:53,137 --> 00:20:54,040
What are you doing?

307
00:20:54,248 --> 00:20:55,340
I'm helping you cut them.

308
00:21:08,970 --> 00:21:10,230
Did you do that on purpose?

309
00:21:12,820 --> 00:21:15,220
Did you remember
I cut your finger before,

310
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:17,500
so this is payback?

311
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:19,360
I don't remember.

312
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:23,780
It's okay.

313
00:21:24,910 --> 00:21:25,650
Take it slow.

314
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:27,580
From now on,

315
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:29,700
I'm going to teach you
basic life skills.

316
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,080
Brushing your teeth,
washing your hair and face,

317
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:34,640
tying your shoelaces,
mending clothes, and doing laundry.

318
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:37,040
You'll have to
learn to do all these yourself.

319
00:21:39,380 --> 00:21:40,630
There's a reward if you do well.

320
00:21:52,270 --> 00:21:53,520
Pull it up.

321
00:22:06,060 --> 00:22:07,170
Nicely brushed.

322
00:22:07,170 --> 00:22:08,760
- Braised pork.
- Deal.

323
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:15,780
All neat and tidy.

324
00:22:15,780 --> 00:22:18,137
Fang Muyang, how do you learn so fast?

325
00:22:18,310 --> 00:22:18,880
Pork cutlet.

326
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:22,130
We don't have that.

327
00:22:22,271 --> 00:22:23,804
Deda Western Restaurant does.

328
00:22:26,330 --> 00:22:27,520
Did you remember something?

329
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:29,800
The pork cutlet
at Deda Western Restaurant,

330
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,690
the ice cream and borscht,
Yuhua Restaurant's meatballs,

331
00:22:31,690 --> 00:22:33,250
and the beef noodles
on Shangcheng Street.

332
00:22:33,260 --> 00:22:34,720
Why is it all food?

333
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,310
Didn't you remember anything else?

334
00:22:39,100 --> 00:22:40,020
The train station.

335
00:22:42,340 --> 00:22:43,660
What about the train station?

336
00:22:48,804 --> 00:22:50,580
The brown sugar
pancakes they sell there.

337
00:22:51,471 --> 00:22:53,980
Fang Muyang, you're exactly
the same as when you were little.

338
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:55,410
All you think about is food.

339
00:22:55,770 --> 00:22:56,740
I'll tell my sister

340
00:22:56,782 --> 00:22:58,448
you've been taking great care of me.

341
00:23:00,060 --> 00:23:00,690
Alright.

342
00:23:01,100 --> 00:23:01,780
(University Fund)

343
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:08,450
(Madam Xu)
Hello, your pork cutlet.

344
00:23:09,900 --> 00:23:10,490
Thank you.

345
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:12,340
You're welcome.

346
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:14,820
I'm not eating it.

347
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:17,740
Braised pork.

348
00:23:17,804 --> 00:23:19,240
Beef noodles from Shangcheng Street.

349
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:24,580
Yuhua Restaurant's meatballs,
and borscht.

350
00:23:31,970 --> 00:23:33,410
Washed up nice and clean.

351
00:23:34,020 --> 00:23:34,860
Coffee.

352
00:23:35,860 --> 00:23:36,580
Co-what?

353
00:23:36,950 --> 00:23:37,580
Hello.

354
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,140
You sure you want coffee

355
00:23:39,140 --> 00:23:40,830
served in this enamel mug?

356
00:23:40,830 --> 00:23:41,650
Yes.

357
00:23:55,070 --> 00:23:55,610
Impressive.

358
00:23:56,190 --> 00:23:57,300
I pricked my hand.

359
00:23:58,370 --> 00:24:00,690
It's fine.
I'll put some antiseptic on it later.

360
00:24:01,890 --> 00:24:02,520
Red...

361
00:24:03,780 --> 00:24:04,550
Remember something?

362
00:24:05,670 --> 00:24:06,693
Red wine.

363
00:24:07,580 --> 00:24:08,290
What?

364
00:24:08,890 --> 00:24:10,060
I want red wine.

365
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:13,420
(Fang Mujing, 100 yuan)

366
00:24:16,982 --> 00:24:19,004
I said I wouldn't spend a cent,
and I won't.

367
00:24:19,590 --> 00:24:20,800
It's not like I'd cheat him.

368
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:24,160
I can earn it back.

369
00:24:41,830 --> 00:24:42,930
One yuan a bottle.

370
00:24:43,210 --> 00:24:43,890
That's right.

371
00:24:49,782 --> 00:24:50,890
I don't want it anymore.

372
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:32,650
So salty and spicy.

373
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:34,960
Maybe...

374
00:25:35,850 --> 00:25:37,970
the grapes weren't great this year.
Just make do.

375
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:38,860
I'm off to work.

376
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:40,030
I want to hear music.

377
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:42,640
Fang Muyang, don't push it.

378
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,930
I'll tell my sister

379
00:25:44,382 --> 00:25:46,115
you've been taking great care of me.

380
00:25:49,020 --> 00:25:49,930
Just one minute.

381
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:21,940
Have him take his medicine.

382
00:26:21,940 --> 00:26:22,210
Okay.

383
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:28,860
Take your medicine.

384
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:41,650
You're leaving?

385
00:26:42,850 --> 00:26:44,450
Yeah, heading home for dinner.

386
00:26:44,626 --> 00:26:45,920
I've got the night shift later.

387
00:26:47,140 --> 00:26:48,860
Can you help trim my nails again?

388
00:26:49,850 --> 00:26:50,280
I...

389
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:51,890
I...

390
00:26:52,470 --> 00:26:53,980
Didn't I already teach you?

391
00:26:53,980 --> 00:26:55,300
You learned it.

392
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:56,820
I forgot again.

393
00:26:58,140 --> 00:26:59,300
I've been biting them off.

394
00:27:05,650 --> 00:27:06,540
Alright, alright.

395
00:27:06,540 --> 00:27:08,370
Stop biting. Sit down.

396
00:27:09,490 --> 00:27:10,530
Take your medicine first.

397
00:27:19,430 --> 00:27:20,270
Look.

398
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:22,820
Just don't go past this line.

399
00:27:23,410 --> 00:27:24,580
Or it'll bleed.

400
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:27,890
See? It comes right off.

401
00:27:31,940 --> 00:27:34,260
Cut along here. See that?

402
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:39,750
Fang Muyang.

403
00:27:42,230 --> 00:27:43,610
Fang Muyang, look at me.

404
00:27:44,070 --> 00:27:44,870
Turn around.

405
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,520
Are you tricking me?

406
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:50,650
You already know how.

407
00:27:50,650 --> 00:27:52,182
You just wanted me to do it for you.

408
00:27:55,300 --> 00:27:55,860
Yes.

409
00:28:01,410 --> 00:28:04,480
Don't think that just because
I buy you food and drinks,

410
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:06,560
and art supplies, it's a given.

411
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:09,010
From now on, every bit of effort
I put in for you

412
00:28:09,010 --> 00:28:10,020
comes with a price.

413
00:28:10,710 --> 00:28:12,060
Everything I've done,

414
00:28:13,293 --> 00:28:14,404
I'll let it slide.

415
00:28:14,850 --> 00:28:17,880
From today onward, it's fixed rates.

416
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:19,490
Actually,

417
00:28:20,210 --> 00:28:21,670
things like trimming nails,

418
00:28:21,670 --> 00:28:22,790
tidying clothes,

419
00:28:22,790 --> 00:28:24,480
these don't really cost anything.

420
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:26,010
I shouldn't be charging you for them.

421
00:28:26,170 --> 00:28:28,440
It's also a task
assigned to me by the factory.

422
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,240
But,

423
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:31,370
if I teach you more than three times

424
00:28:31,370 --> 00:28:32,400
and you still can't learn,

425
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:33,780
then I'll charge per session.

426
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:37,880
Also, when you buy
sketchbooks and art supplies,

427
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:40,150
or anything you want to eat,
like fried pork cutlet,

428
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,580
coffee,

429
00:28:41,850 --> 00:28:42,770
or wine,

430
00:28:42,770 --> 00:28:44,500
it all gets deducted
from the hundred yuan.

431
00:28:44,780 --> 00:28:45,540
Agreed?

432
00:28:54,110 --> 00:28:54,940
Look here.

433
00:28:55,450 --> 00:28:57,370
Nail trimming, clothes tidying,

434
00:28:57,370 --> 00:28:59,190
(Fee Schedule)
shaving, three cents each time.

435
00:29:00,370 --> 00:29:03,100
Hair washing, sponge baths,
laundry, sewing buttons,

436
00:29:03,100 --> 00:29:04,170
ten cents each time.

437
00:29:04,340 --> 00:29:06,260
Food, drink, clothing,
and daily expenses

438
00:29:06,582 --> 00:29:07,915
are reimbursed as spent.

439
00:29:08,980 --> 00:29:10,260
You nodded just now.

440
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:12,540
Sign here.

441
00:29:14,940 --> 00:29:17,140
(Both Parties Sign)

442
00:29:17,970 --> 00:29:18,890
The name.

443
00:29:20,210 --> 00:29:21,170
How do I write it?

444
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:42,800
Nail trimming.

445
00:29:49,630 --> 00:29:50,580
I'm charging you now.

446
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:52,460
Go ahead.

447
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:54,570
Okay.

448
00:29:59,060 --> 00:30:00,320
Speaking of money,

449
00:30:00,320 --> 00:30:01,580
I just remembered.

450
00:30:01,730 --> 00:30:04,390
You still owed me money
back in middle school.

451
00:30:04,740 --> 00:30:05,260
Don't run.

452
00:30:05,260 --> 00:30:08,380
(Six Years Earlier)

453
00:30:14,210 --> 00:30:16,650
Fei Ni, I've got no money for food.

454
00:30:16,650 --> 00:30:17,680
Lend me some?

455
00:30:18,780 --> 00:30:20,870
Don't your family give you money?

456
00:30:25,780 --> 00:30:27,130
How much do you want?

457
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:28,430
How much do you have?

458
00:30:36,690 --> 00:30:37,390
This little?

459
00:30:37,390 --> 00:30:39,337
It's not even enough
for one brown sugar cake.

460
00:30:39,410 --> 00:30:41,170
Just give me everything you've got.

461
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:42,680
I'll pay you back double.

462
00:30:44,780 --> 00:30:45,660
Really?

463
00:30:45,660 --> 00:30:46,520
Of course.

464
00:30:46,780 --> 00:30:47,820
If you don't believe me,

465
00:30:47,820 --> 00:30:49,470
I'll leave my sketchbook as collateral.

466
00:30:49,650 --> 00:30:50,890
I've got no use for that.

467
00:30:55,937 --> 00:30:57,120
When my grandma gets back,

468
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:59,660
I'll buy you a chocolate and cream cake.

469
00:30:59,900 --> 00:31:01,280
No need to treat me.

470
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:02,150
Just pay me back.

471
00:31:02,300 --> 00:31:03,060
Thanks.

472
00:31:04,950 --> 00:31:05,690
Here.

473
00:31:06,170 --> 00:31:07,900
Borrowed five cents,
paying back ten.

474
00:31:08,340 --> 00:31:08,980
Double, right?

475
00:31:09,320 --> 00:31:09,860
Okay.

476
00:31:11,915 --> 00:31:13,450
Can you lend me another twenty cents?

477
00:31:14,010 --> 00:31:14,940
I'll pay you back forty,

478
00:31:14,940 --> 00:31:16,500
and treat you to a brown sugar pancake.

479
00:31:18,780 --> 00:31:20,170
You're broke again?

480
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:21,430
Didn't I just repay you?

481
00:31:21,820 --> 00:31:23,950
Besides, I'll have money
once my grandma's back.

482
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:26,890
Skip the pancake.

483
00:31:27,020 --> 00:31:28,200
By your rules,

484
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:29,230
just pay me forty.

485
00:31:30,020 --> 00:31:31,300
A promise is a promise.

486
00:31:32,020 --> 00:31:32,950
When?

487
00:31:34,390 --> 00:31:35,030
Sunday.

488
00:31:35,500 --> 00:31:36,330
I'll come find you.

489
00:31:37,290 --> 00:31:38,070
Where do you live?

490
00:31:38,620 --> 00:31:42,220
(Jiangcheng No. 1
Textile Factory Family Quarters)

491
00:31:44,580 --> 00:31:46,370
Come on, let's go play at Jingshan Park.

492
00:31:46,370 --> 00:31:47,610
- Okay.
- Okay.

493
00:31:47,810 --> 00:31:48,640
My mom said

494
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,580
Jingshan Park is gorgeous
this time of year.

495
00:31:50,810 --> 00:31:51,450
Yeah!

496
00:31:51,630 --> 00:31:53,500
My mom said
all the flowers are blooming.

497
00:31:53,700 --> 00:31:54,630
Then let's go.

498
00:31:54,630 --> 00:31:55,370
Come on!

499
00:31:56,370 --> 00:31:57,580
Fei Ni, you coming?

500
00:31:58,480 --> 00:32:00,020
I'll pass. You guys go ahead.

501
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:01,715
- Okay!
- Let's go!

502
00:32:43,370 --> 00:32:45,700
Fei Ni, dinner's ready.

503
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:54,170
I won't bother
with all those years of interest.

504
00:32:54,170 --> 00:32:55,590
You've got money now.

505
00:32:55,590 --> 00:32:57,330
Why don't we settle up?

506
00:32:59,090 --> 00:32:59,810
I don't remember.

507
00:33:01,780 --> 00:33:02,690
Fine.

508
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:05,120
You will someday.

509
00:33:11,580 --> 00:33:12,580
Fang Muyang.

510
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,930
I already washed these.

511
00:33:14,930 --> 00:33:16,210
Why did you wash them again?

512
00:33:17,740 --> 00:33:19,370
You said I should learn.

513
00:33:21,360 --> 00:33:21,800
I...

514
00:33:23,460 --> 00:33:24,780
I told you to learn,

515
00:33:25,590 --> 00:33:26,930
not ruin them.

516
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:30,580
How am I supposed to fix this now?

517
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:35,100
And you're laughing?

518
00:33:41,580 --> 00:33:42,240
Ni.

519
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:42,840
Yeah?

520
00:33:44,210 --> 00:33:45,430
What are you doing?

521
00:33:45,430 --> 00:33:47,370
Those are from ten years ago.

522
00:33:47,370 --> 00:33:48,740
Why dig them out?

523
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:52,610
I'm making Fang Muyang a shirt.

524
00:33:53,170 --> 00:33:54,300
Be serious.

525
00:33:54,490 --> 00:33:56,900
Look at his build,

526
00:33:56,900 --> 00:33:57,960
and look at mine.

527
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:00,880
I'll just add a bit to the length.

528
00:34:04,300 --> 00:34:04,800
Well,

529
00:34:05,500 --> 00:34:08,510
my daughter's got
brains and good hands.

530
00:34:49,540 --> 00:34:53,460
(Save the Dying, Heal the Wounded
Serving Workers and Peasants)

531
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:57,520
The fabric's old,

532
00:34:58,200 --> 00:35:00,810
but buying new cloth
and making one from scratch

533
00:35:00,810 --> 00:35:01,930
would cost a lot.

534
00:35:01,930 --> 00:35:03,493
And you don't have fabric coupons.

535
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:05,410
So?

536
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:06,900
It's unique.

537
00:35:07,490 --> 00:35:08,500
Nice color too.

538
00:35:09,170 --> 00:35:10,070
Color...

539
00:35:10,700 --> 00:35:11,410
Mom,

540
00:35:11,510 --> 00:35:13,480
where are the cloth scraps?

541
00:35:17,510 --> 00:35:18,260
Looks good, right?

542
00:35:18,670 --> 00:35:20,090
I picked it out carefully.

543
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,220
Since you seem happy with it,

544
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:24,204
I'll charge you two yuan.

545
00:35:27,220 --> 00:35:28,050
What?

546
00:35:28,670 --> 00:35:30,920
It'd cost more in a shop.

547
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:32,248
I'm already giving you a deal.

548
00:35:32,893 --> 00:35:33,710
I don't want it.

549
00:35:33,710 --> 00:35:34,700
Wait, wait.

550
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,480
One fifty. That's my final offer.

551
00:35:42,020 --> 00:35:43,050
Fang Muyang.

552
00:35:44,170 --> 00:35:45,950
So you've learned to bargain now?

553
00:35:46,010 --> 00:35:46,730
You taught me.

554
00:35:49,180 --> 00:35:49,700
Fair enough.

555
00:35:49,700 --> 00:35:51,550
That's a useful skill.

556
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:52,830
You'll need it.

557
00:35:54,580 --> 00:35:56,200
Look at this.

558
00:35:57,010 --> 00:35:58,410
I restocked everything for you.

559
00:35:59,610 --> 00:36:01,560
Draw and think wisely.

560
00:36:01,920 --> 00:36:03,270
Or I've wasted my money.

561
00:36:03,740 --> 00:36:04,300
I have money.

562
00:36:04,720 --> 00:36:06,050
That doesn't mean you waste it.

563
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:07,060
Wait.

564
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:09,490
I'll draw you.

565
00:36:12,190 --> 00:36:13,250
Why me?

566
00:36:13,540 --> 00:36:14,730
You told me to draw.

567
00:36:16,970 --> 00:36:17,530
I...

568
00:36:17,890 --> 00:36:18,410
Fine.

569
00:36:33,860 --> 00:36:34,560
Turn a bit.

570
00:36:57,620 --> 00:36:58,370
Fang Muyang,

571
00:36:59,090 --> 00:37:00,100
you really don't remember

572
00:37:00,100 --> 00:37:01,460
anything from school?

573
00:37:03,180 --> 00:37:04,660
You scared me with that dead fly,

574
00:37:05,010 --> 00:37:06,220
and I twisted my ankle.

575
00:37:06,430 --> 00:37:09,420
And that time you splashed mud
all over me on your bike.

576
00:37:09,980 --> 00:37:11,940
With genes like yours,

577
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:13,650
your mom's a university lecturer,

578
00:37:13,650 --> 00:37:15,210
your dad's a famous painter,

579
00:37:15,210 --> 00:37:16,920
how did none of that pass on to you?

580
00:37:16,920 --> 00:37:18,271
You even had to repeat a year.

581
00:37:36,260 --> 00:37:37,780
You look good when you smile.

582
00:37:37,940 --> 00:37:41,740
♪Summer, by my ears♪

583
00:37:42,300 --> 00:37:46,100
♪The wind sweeps
through the wheat fields♪

584
00:37:47,140 --> 00:37:51,460
♪Cicadas sing on the treetops♪

585
00:37:51,580 --> 00:37:55,020
♪Writing the language of youth♪

586
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:59,220
♪Smiles in my eyes♪

587
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:03,700
♪Sweet as if dipped in honey♪

588
00:38:04,660 --> 00:38:08,260
♪Watching the sunset♪

589
00:38:08,300 --> 00:38:12,500
♪Stain the passing years red♪

590
00:38:13,380 --> 00:38:16,940
♪Talk a little, listen a little♪

591
00:38:17,060 --> 00:38:20,940
♪Let time settle♪

592
00:38:22,180 --> 00:38:25,820
♪Feel the warm breeze♪

593
00:38:26,020 --> 00:38:29,300
♪Carry us into tomorrow♪

594
00:38:29,300 --> 00:38:30,220
For you.

595
00:38:31,220 --> 00:38:34,540
♪When someday, some promise♪

596
00:38:37,660 --> 00:38:39,740
Your drawing is amazing.

597
00:38:40,260 --> 00:38:43,180
It looks just like a studio photograph.

598
00:38:43,510 --> 00:38:45,270
How much does a photo cost at a studio?

599
00:38:46,660 --> 00:38:48,660
For one this size,

600
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:50,780
about one yuan.

601
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:53,510
I'll charge you fifty cents.

602
00:38:57,010 --> 00:38:58,900
Fang Muyang,
now you're making money off me?

603
00:38:58,960 --> 00:39:00,180
You taught me.

604
00:39:00,890 --> 00:39:02,260
You messing with me?

605
00:39:02,510 --> 00:39:04,170
At this rate,

606
00:39:04,170 --> 00:39:05,490
your memory should be back soon.

607
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:07,182
I'll draw you every day.

608
00:39:07,410 --> 00:39:07,980
No charge.

609
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:12,390
No need.

610
00:39:13,430 --> 00:39:14,500
One is enough.

611
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:16,320
Some things

612
00:39:16,715 --> 00:39:18,271
are more precious with rarity.

613
00:39:19,950 --> 00:39:20,860
I like it.

614
00:39:21,240 --> 00:39:21,860
Thanks.

615
00:39:28,410 --> 00:39:28,860
Oh, right,

616
00:39:29,550 --> 00:39:31,440
I'll take you to
meet someone this weekend.

617
00:39:31,790 --> 00:39:32,320
Okay.

618
00:39:33,780 --> 00:39:35,426
You don't want to know who?

619
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:37,660
Not really.

620
00:39:38,830 --> 00:39:40,240
I wouldn't remember anyway.

621
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:44,180
I'll grab you a carrot.

622
00:40:08,710 --> 00:40:09,660
Everyone, watch closely.

623
00:40:09,671 --> 00:40:11,410
(Fei Ting)
Planting rice seedlings is simple.

624
00:40:11,600 --> 00:40:13,700
Shallow water, shallow planting.

625
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:15,093
Plant them steadily and straight.

626
00:40:15,137 --> 00:40:16,680
One thing to watch out for

627
00:40:16,760 --> 00:40:19,050
is not to plant them too deeply.

628
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:21,770
They'll drown in a few days.

629
00:40:21,915 --> 00:40:22,804
One more thing.

630
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:24,980
Mind the gap between each seedling...

631
00:40:24,980 --> 00:40:26,640
Fei Ting, Fei Ting.

632
00:40:28,300 --> 00:40:29,400
Your partner's on the phone.

633
00:40:29,610 --> 00:40:30,890
Go take it at the commune.

634
00:40:31,530 --> 00:40:31,990
Coming.

635
00:40:33,390 --> 00:40:34,220
You all try first.

636
00:40:44,830 --> 00:40:45,380
Hello?

637
00:40:46,070 --> 00:40:46,640
Fei Ting,

638
00:40:47,330 --> 00:40:48,400
is the return report ready?

639
00:40:49,520 --> 00:40:50,200
I...

640
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:51,780
I got it.

641
00:40:52,190 --> 00:40:53,180
I got it ready.

642
00:40:54,100 --> 00:40:55,270
So why no updates?

643
00:40:55,850 --> 00:40:58,870
No. There's been
a lot of work in the fields lately.

644
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:00,260
Everyone's swamped.

645
00:41:00,560 --> 00:41:02,400
The regiment leader
hasn't had time for this.

646
00:41:02,620 --> 00:41:04,080
Maybe give it a bit longer.

647
00:41:04,080 --> 00:41:05,570
Don't dodge the question.

648
00:41:05,570 --> 00:41:07,490
Your fracture never healed properly.

649
00:41:07,515 --> 00:41:09,048
Your medical discharge was approved.

650
00:41:09,071 --> 00:41:10,150
Is the leader too busy,

651
00:41:10,150 --> 00:41:11,820
or did you never submit the report?

652
00:41:18,060 --> 00:41:19,340
Fei Ting, be honest with me.

653
00:41:20,130 --> 00:41:21,620
Did you never plan to come back?

654
00:41:22,250 --> 00:41:23,890
Did you never plan to marry me?

655
00:41:24,240 --> 00:41:26,100
If that's the case, just say it.

656
00:41:26,100 --> 00:41:27,250
If we're done, so be it.

657
00:41:27,350 --> 00:41:28,800
I'm not clinging to you.

658
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:32,404
Go find someone else then.

659
00:41:32,820 --> 00:41:33,690
I'm not going back.

660
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:39,790
Fine. I will.

661
00:41:51,460 --> 00:41:56,740
(Jiangcheng University)

662
00:41:56,740 --> 00:41:57,780
Spread out.

663
00:42:04,620 --> 00:42:05,820
Stop reading for a second.

664
00:42:05,820 --> 00:42:07,740
The one who just scored was Ye Feng.

665
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:12,448
His mom's the administration director
at Jiangcheng No. 1 Textile Factory.

666
00:42:24,660 --> 00:42:26,050
Come on, let's return the books.

667
00:42:30,700 --> 00:42:31,300
Hua,

668
00:42:31,570 --> 00:42:33,370
I just remembered
I've got something to do.

669
00:42:33,370 --> 00:42:34,410
Can you return them for me?

670
00:42:34,620 --> 00:42:35,140
Sure.

671
00:42:46,450 --> 00:42:47,740
Move it to the side.

672
00:42:48,140 --> 00:42:48,690
To the side.

673
00:42:49,140 --> 00:42:50,380
Shift it over!

674
00:42:53,370 --> 00:42:54,140
Careful.

675
00:42:56,530 --> 00:42:57,700
Hey, are you okay?

676
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:03,050
I'm fine.

677
00:43:05,640 --> 00:43:06,820
Fine? It's already red.

678
00:43:08,090 --> 00:43:09,580
Zu, cover for me a sec.

679
00:43:10,050 --> 00:43:11,450
Let's go to the infirmary. Come.

680
00:43:28,860 --> 00:43:33,340
♪After the laughter, I think of you♪

681
00:43:35,900 --> 00:43:40,620
♪After the storm, I think of you♪

682
00:43:43,140 --> 00:43:49,260
♪In the little courtyard,
there you are dancing♪

683
00:43:50,260 --> 00:43:54,820
♪That earnest you,
smiling so innocently♪

684
00:43:57,300 --> 00:44:02,060
♪In spring, I stay by your side♪

685
00:44:04,500 --> 00:44:08,860
♪When summer comes, I watch over you♪

686
00:44:11,220 --> 00:44:17,860
♪In the light of dawn, you belong to me♪

687
00:44:17,860 --> 00:44:27,460
♪At the edge of the world,
I will still hold you tight♪

688
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:34,700
♪There is a small place♪

689
00:44:34,700 --> 00:44:41,500
♪Where they carry big dreams♪

690
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:48,860
♪Every lovely face♪

691
00:44:49,740 --> 00:44:55,900
♪Shines brightly in the heart♪

692
00:44:56,700 --> 00:45:02,740
♪Even when we collide,
we hold our course♪

693
00:45:03,940 --> 00:45:09,740
♪Even when we stumble,
we keep our resolve♪

694
00:45:10,820 --> 00:45:17,100
♪My you, walking toward the distance♪

695
00:45:17,900 --> 00:45:26,140
♪Please carry our dreams
and let them soar♪
